03:38.941 --> 03:40.711
Irving: Offering a fat reward
wouldn't hurt, sir.

03:40.811 --> 03:42.880
Tenzer: I was also thinking
we should bring in the marshals

03:42.980 --> 03:43.881
and the bureau.

03:43.981 --> 03:45.984
Chief, I'd say negative
on the feds.

03:46.084 --> 03:47.285
Our mess,
we clean it up.

03:47.385 --> 03:49.087
You're probably right, Irv.
What else?

03:49.187 --> 03:50.555
Well, if I may, sir,

03:50.655 --> 03:53.559
I'd suggest putting together
a fugitive task force.

03:53.659 --> 03:56.229
Off the top of my head,
I'd say it's a good idea.

03:56.329 --> 03:57.898
I'll get back to you
on that asap.

03:57.998 --> 03:59.365
That'd be all, chief?

03:59.500 --> 04:00.935
Bit hectic on this end,
as you could imagine.

04:01.035 --> 04:03.137
Of course, Irv. All for now.
Have a better one.

04:03.237 --> 04:04.305
[ Dial tone ]

04:04.405 --> 04:05.807
[ Telephone beeps ]

04:05.908 --> 04:07.142
Asshole.

04:07.242 --> 04:09.077
Popeil: ...Incredible deal.

04:09.177 --> 04:12.516
If you help us advertise this
fabulous showtime knife pack,

04:12.549 --> 04:16.086
you'll also receive
my latest invention free.

04:16.186 --> 04:18.889
It's the showtime
solid flavor injector.

04:18.989 --> 04:21.960
Come on over here, and
I'll show you how this works.

04:22.060 --> 04:25.531
Now, this is
my new solid flavor injector.

04:25.597 --> 04:27.800
Over here, I have...

04:27.900 --> 04:32.239
[Narration continues
indistinctly]

04:37.712 --> 04:41.551
I'll take it,
and I'll plunge it in,

04:41.584 --> 04:44.554
and I'll just inject it
right into the center.

04:44.654 --> 04:46.823
It's as easy as that.

04:46.923 --> 04:50.961
I was on live television with
the solid flavor injector...

04:51.061 --> 04:52.129
Oh!

04:52.229 --> 04:53.565
You left
the door unlocked.

04:53.665 --> 04:56.401
[ Sighs ] David!

04:56.569 --> 04:58.103
[ Chuckles ]
You're home.

04:58.203 --> 05:00.372
Ma, the back door --

05:00.573 --> 05:02.876
you left it unlocked.
It's not safe.

05:02.976 --> 05:05.444
Well, I opened the door
to get some fresh air.

05:05.579 --> 05:07.848
But I will be
more careful.

05:07.948 --> 05:09.249
I hope so.

05:09.349 --> 05:11.251
How was your trip,
David?

05:11.351 --> 05:13.989
I don't know.

05:14.089 --> 05:15.490
Tiring.

05:15.591 --> 05:17.259
You know, mom, I thought
I'd come stay with you

05:17.359 --> 05:19.161
for the holidays,
if that's okay.

05:19.261 --> 05:22.132
Oh. Oh,
of course it's okay.

05:22.232 --> 05:23.601
You are
more than welcome.

05:23.701 --> 05:25.135
Stay as long
as you like.

05:25.235 --> 05:27.271
Thank you.
[ Chuckles ]

05:27.371 --> 05:29.140
Merci beaucoup.

05:29.240 --> 05:30.308
De rein.

05:30.408 --> 05:32.878
[ Both chuckle ]

05:32.978 --> 05:34.847
Oh.

05:34.947 --> 05:37.618
I think I've run out
of my lupus medications.

05:37.684 --> 05:39.686
Yeah, it looks like it.

05:39.786 --> 05:41.855
Looks like you got
a little flare-up.

05:41.956 --> 05:43.390
Mm.

05:43.490 --> 05:45.793
Well, I'll take care of it
tomorrow.

05:48.496 --> 05:50.699
Are you hungry?
Should I make dinner?

05:50.799 --> 05:53.536
I am a little peckish.

05:53.637 --> 05:55.471
[ Chuckles ]
No string beans.

05:55.639 --> 05:58.743
No, no string beans.

06:00.745 --> 06:03.214
Here you go.

06:03.314 --> 06:04.916
What a great holiday gift.

06:05.016 --> 06:07.253
Call now, and you can finish
all your gift shopping

06:07.353 --> 06:10.890
for any holiday
with one toll-free call.
[ Sighs ]

06:10.990 --> 06:13.661
[ Ventilator hissing ]
Woman:
Cardiology on call to the O.R.

06:13.761 --> 06:16.363
Cardiology on call
to the O.R.

06:32.817 --> 06:35.486
Barrel, wake up.

06:35.586 --> 06:37.421
Oh.

06:37.522 --> 06:39.257
Harry.

06:39.357 --> 06:41.126
Go home.
Get some sleep.

06:43.029 --> 06:45.732
What about you?
I'm wide awake.

06:49.236 --> 06:51.739
Okay, thanks.

06:56.745 --> 06:58.247
How's he doing?

06:58.347 --> 06:59.716
Still ticking.

06:59.749 --> 07:02.018
He's tough.

07:02.118 --> 07:05.022
That he is.

07:06.890 --> 07:09.627
That's
one fucking bad break.

07:09.728 --> 07:11.262
Thanks, pal.

07:11.362 --> 07:15.167
...to radiology.
Dr. sherman to radiology.

07:24.846 --> 07:27.014
[ Indistinct conversations ]

07:37.126 --> 07:38.328
Chief.

07:38.428 --> 07:39.830
How's detective Moore?

07:39.930 --> 07:41.498
Not out of the woods yet.

07:41.598 --> 07:44.635
District attorney held
his press conference last night.

07:44.770 --> 07:46.304
I heard.

07:46.404 --> 07:50.142
He dwelt at length on the fact
that we let waits get away.

07:50.242 --> 07:53.380
In an hour, I'll be announcing
a fugitive task force

07:53.480 --> 07:54.614
to apprehend waits.

07:54.782 --> 07:56.583
Captain pounds
will be in command.

07:56.683 --> 07:57.951
Pounds?

07:58.051 --> 07:59.954
I thought the idea
was to apprehend waits.

08:00.054 --> 08:02.190
You're to have no part
of that task force, detective,

08:02.290 --> 08:04.059
or that investigation.
Is that understood?

08:04.159 --> 08:06.295
You're throwing me
to the wolves, chief.

08:06.395 --> 08:08.799
Detective in charge of the field
trip is left off the task force.

08:08.865 --> 08:10.566
What's that say?

08:10.666 --> 08:13.103
I know too well your propensity
for operating ad hoc, bosch.

08:13.203 --> 08:15.139
Not this time.

08:15.239 --> 08:17.708
You want to help
the department and yourself?

08:17.809 --> 08:19.077
Close your case.

08:19.177 --> 08:21.814
Find out who really killed
the delacroix boy.

08:21.847 --> 08:24.317
Prove waits was lying
from the start

08:24.417 --> 08:28.221
and that o'shea...Was a fool
for believing him.

08:28.321 --> 08:30.825
[ Engine turns over ]

08:41.170 --> 08:43.205
Look at this.

08:43.305 --> 08:44.541
L.T. Pair you up?

08:44.641 --> 08:46.076
Yeah, for
the waits task force.

08:46.176 --> 08:47.878
Till crate
comes off the d.L.

08:47.978 --> 08:49.113
Thought I sent you home
to get some sleep.

08:49.213 --> 08:50.849
I'll sleep
when this is over.

08:50.949 --> 08:52.183
I did change my shirt.

08:52.283 --> 08:54.119
I want to look my best
for the cameras

08:54.219 --> 08:55.720
when we catch
that asshole.

08:55.855 --> 08:57.356
You could use a fresh one,
too, Harry.

08:57.456 --> 08:58.891
You're kind of ripe.

08:58.991 --> 09:00.293
[ Sniffs ]
Oh!

09:00.393 --> 09:02.328
[ Chuckles ]

09:02.428 --> 09:05.332
[ Police radio chatter ]

09:07.768 --> 09:09.237
Harry.

09:12.941 --> 09:14.477
What's up?
Check it out.

09:14.577 --> 09:16.880
Now I'd like to introduce
deputy chief Irving...

09:16.946 --> 09:19.716
Ohh!
...Who will oversee
this task force.

09:19.884 --> 09:22.619
Oh, yeah,
tenzer's teeing up Irving

09:22.719 --> 09:24.489
for his big moment
in the sun.

09:24.589 --> 09:26.791
Thank you, chief tenzer.

09:26.892 --> 09:29.896
Before I introduce
captain pounds,

09:29.962 --> 09:32.098
I'd just like to assure
the people of Los Angeles

09:32.198 --> 09:34.767
that every effort is being made
to apprehend this criminal.

09:34.902 --> 09:37.304
I don't get it.
I don't get it.

09:37.404 --> 09:40.041
Why is Irving putting pounds
in charge of the posse?

09:40.141 --> 09:41.675
Doesn't he want to catch
this fucking guy?

09:41.775 --> 09:43.311
Exactly what
i said to him before.

09:43.411 --> 09:44.679
What'd he say?

09:44.779 --> 09:46.048
Told me to mind
my own business, so, I have.

09:46.148 --> 09:48.217
Edgar and I are headed out
to the valley

09:48.317 --> 09:50.320
to interview
Arthur delacroix's father.

09:50.420 --> 09:52.022
But I wish them
the best of luck.

09:52.122 --> 09:54.324
Oh, I almost forgot.
Uh, visitor.

09:54.424 --> 09:56.593
I stashed her
in the l.T.'S office.

09:56.693 --> 09:58.295
Christine waters.

10:01.433 --> 10:02.767
Mrs. waters?

10:02.867 --> 10:05.671
Detective,
i know you're busy.

10:05.771 --> 10:08.474
I wish you'd called.
I'm on my way out.

10:08.574 --> 10:09.977
I'm sorry.

10:10.077 --> 10:11.811
I just wanted to ask
a quick question in person,

10:11.912 --> 10:13.680
not over the phone.

10:13.780 --> 10:16.017
That's fine.
Sit down.

10:18.920 --> 10:20.923
What can I do for you?

10:21.023 --> 10:23.525
[ Sighs ]

10:23.625 --> 10:24.994
I've been following
the news.

10:25.095 --> 10:29.799
This man, this waits person,
did he kill my son?

10:29.899 --> 10:31.169
Did he kill Arthur?

10:31.269 --> 10:34.238
We don't know yet.
We're still investigating.

10:34.338 --> 10:36.508
What's
your personal opinion?

10:39.979 --> 10:42.282
Your son was abused
for years.

10:42.382 --> 10:44.550
His injuries were chronic
and severe.

10:44.650 --> 10:46.187
So,
it's logical to suspect

10:46.287 --> 10:48.089
that his death is connected
to that abuse

10:48.189 --> 10:50.993
and not some random encounter
with a stranger.

10:51.093 --> 10:52.294
You suspect
Arthur's father?

10:52.394 --> 10:54.896
As I said,
we're still investigating.

10:54.997 --> 10:57.633
But this waits person
confessed.

10:57.733 --> 11:00.036
But we're not entirely convinced
he was telling the truth.

11:03.907 --> 11:05.576
Thank you for your time,
detective.

11:05.676 --> 11:07.012
Of course.

11:07.045 --> 11:09.114
[ Sighs ]

11:09.214 --> 11:11.050
[ Sniffles softly ]

11:11.150 --> 11:14.520
All these years,
I've had this daydream

11:14.620 --> 11:18.558
that my children were okay
and doing well,

11:18.658 --> 11:21.062
even thriving without me.

11:21.162 --> 11:22.930
That I'd see them again
some day,

11:23.031 --> 11:24.432
and that
they'd forgive me.

11:24.532 --> 11:27.469
Mrs. waters,
the situation you were in,

11:27.569 --> 11:30.305
it must have been very difficult
to know what to do.

11:30.405 --> 11:33.543
Oh, I knew
what I was doing.

11:35.445 --> 11:38.349
I saved myself
at their expense.

11:40.084 --> 11:42.187
Not too late to go visit
your daughter.

11:42.287 --> 11:43.588
While you're still here.

11:46.825 --> 11:48.894
[ Scoffs softly ]

11:49.062 --> 11:51.765
[ Voice breaking ]
I'm afraid it is.

12:02.444 --> 12:04.180
Oh!

12:04.280 --> 12:07.150
Oh, my pills, dear.
The -- the round one, please.

12:07.250 --> 12:08.618
Whoa! [ Chuckles ]
Dizzy.

12:08.718 --> 12:11.555
No, ma. Ma, it's triangles
for the dizzies.

12:11.655 --> 12:13.724
It's the round ones
for pain, remember?

12:13.824 --> 12:16.428
Are you sure?
Yes. Yes, I'm sure.

12:16.528 --> 12:19.231
I wrote it down for you.
It's on the fridge.

12:19.331 --> 12:22.102
Oh, put the TV on,
dear.

12:23.869 --> 12:25.671
[ TV turns on ]

12:25.771 --> 12:28.109
Oh, t-turn it up,
please.

12:28.175 --> 12:32.914
Oh, a-and my -- my glasses.
Have you seen my glasses?

12:33.014 --> 12:35.517
I...I-i can't find them
anywhere.

12:35.617 --> 12:37.120
Nope.

12:37.220 --> 12:41.625
Oh! Would you do
my pills, please?

12:41.725 --> 12:43.193
Mm-hmm.

12:43.293 --> 12:45.429
I went through the week's worth
while you were gone,

12:45.529 --> 12:47.632
and I was very confused
by the eighth day.

12:47.732 --> 12:51.136
Ma, after I do your meds,
i have to go out for awhile.

12:51.169 --> 12:54.005
Why?
Um, for work.

12:54.140 --> 12:55.541
But i-i won't
be gone long.

12:55.641 --> 12:57.644
But it's the holidays.

12:57.744 --> 13:00.613
I mean, don't these people know
that you have family?

13:00.713 --> 13:02.150
Ma.

13:02.250 --> 13:05.319
Windows can wait!
Look, it's my busy season.

13:05.419 --> 13:07.289
Make hay
while the sun shines.

13:07.389 --> 13:09.224
Isn't that
what you always say?

13:09.324 --> 13:11.593
Well, maybe it'll rain.

13:11.693 --> 13:13.163
Then you don't
have to wash windows.

13:13.229 --> 13:14.697
You can stay with me.

13:16.532 --> 13:17.734
Hmm.

13:19.436 --> 13:21.972
Edgar: You've made up your mind
about the father, right?

13:22.073 --> 13:23.541
He's the one?

13:23.641 --> 13:25.577
Who else kicked the shit out
of that kid every day?

13:25.677 --> 13:27.880
Waits' confession?

13:27.980 --> 13:29.582
That was him
gaming the system.

13:29.682 --> 13:31.950
It worked.

13:32.050 --> 13:34.188
But I always try
to keep an open mind

13:34.254 --> 13:36.190
about suspects
and witnesses.

13:38.092 --> 13:40.395
[ Dog barks in distance ]

13:53.277 --> 13:55.045
[ Cat meowing ]

13:55.213 --> 13:59.284
Aww.
That's buddy boy.

13:59.384 --> 14:02.020
He's looking for a treat.
[ Chuckles ]

14:02.120 --> 14:04.424
[ Cat meows ]

14:04.524 --> 14:05.958
Buddy.

14:06.058 --> 14:07.961
About Arthur,
Mr. delacroix,

14:08.061 --> 14:10.964
we were hoping you might be able
to give us some background

14:11.064 --> 14:13.368
on your boy, maybe some names.
We're trying to track down

14:13.468 --> 14:15.002
some of his friends
from back then.

14:15.102 --> 14:16.538
We need to talk to anybody
who might know

14:16.638 --> 14:18.241
where he went
the day he disappeared.

14:18.307 --> 14:20.042
It was a long time ago.

14:20.142 --> 14:21.477
The picture.

14:21.577 --> 14:23.680
[ Sighs ]

14:32.257 --> 14:34.025
[ Inhales sharply ]

14:34.125 --> 14:36.728
[ Sighs ]

14:36.828 --> 14:38.665
[ Voice breaking ]
Where'd you get this?

14:38.765 --> 14:40.166
Your daughter.

14:40.267 --> 14:43.070
My daughter?

14:43.170 --> 14:45.406
[ Exhales softly ]

14:45.506 --> 14:46.907
What'd she say about me?

14:47.007 --> 14:50.178
We mostly talked
about Arthur.

14:50.279 --> 14:51.913
Could you
look at the photo?

14:54.484 --> 14:56.452
Yeah, that's them.

14:56.552 --> 14:58.053
He didn't have
any other friends,

14:58.154 --> 15:01.292
just these bums
he skateboarded with.

15:01.358 --> 15:03.026
The photo, sir.

15:03.126 --> 15:05.096
If you remember any names.

15:05.196 --> 15:07.365
Maybe.

15:09.635 --> 15:11.670
[ Chuckles softly ]
That's deuce -- piece of shit.

15:11.770 --> 15:14.408
This one here, that's --
that's pat.

15:14.508 --> 15:16.876
Eh, maybe it was Paul.

15:16.976 --> 15:18.913
[ Sighs ]

15:19.013 --> 15:23.318
The guy in the middle,
Stokes.

15:23.385 --> 15:25.053
Yeah.
Arthur looked up to him.

15:25.153 --> 15:28.357
He was older, a few years.
Big deal when you're that age.

15:28.458 --> 15:30.693
You remember
any last names?

15:32.595 --> 15:35.966
Well, that was
his last name -- Stokes.

15:36.066 --> 15:39.137
Uh, Johnny -- Jimmy.

15:39.237 --> 15:42.807
Something like that.

15:42.907 --> 15:45.545
Bosch: Something else maybe
you could help us with.

15:45.645 --> 15:48.815
There's no record
of any missing-persons report.

15:48.915 --> 15:51.485
What are you talking about?

15:51.585 --> 15:53.354
Of course I reported it.

15:53.387 --> 15:55.690
To who? Not l.A.P.D.

15:55.790 --> 15:58.493
Well, I'm sure I did.
I went to the station.

15:58.593 --> 15:59.662
You might have gone
to the station,

15:59.762 --> 16:01.630
but you didn't file
a report.

16:01.730 --> 16:04.368
Your daughter says you told her
you reported Arthur missing.

16:04.434 --> 16:05.835
You lied to her.

16:07.437 --> 16:09.507
What really happened,
Mr. delacroix?

16:12.777 --> 16:19.486
My boy went to school,
and I never saw him again.

16:19.586 --> 16:20.953
The police did shit.

16:21.053 --> 16:22.855
End of story.

16:22.955 --> 16:25.993
Till they find his body
20 years too late.

16:26.093 --> 16:28.696
Why didn't you report
your son missing that night

